## When to use
When you need to inspect and understand detailed information about your system's CPU and memory usage over time.

## Approach
Use the `shell_exec` tool with the `vmstat` command. Common advanced options include `-w 1 -t` for monitoring updates every second with timestamps, which is useful for tracking resource usage over time. For continuous monitoring of CPU and memory statistics, you can use `vmstat -w 1`.

## Example
```sh
shell_exec "vmstat -w 1"
```
This example uses the `shell_exec` tool to run an `vmstat` command that monitors system resources including CPU and memory usage every second.

## Pitfalls
- Ensure that the system has installed and configured the necessary utilities for running shell commands.
- Be aware of the interval duration when using continuous monitoring as it can generate a large amount of output quickly.